$interpreted: Naya: ... Angel, you really should have seen Sherlock's face back there.

Naya: Trying to take advantage of us and use this opportunity to seize the position of president? 
Ha! Suck on that, you tin can!
Elio: However, since we tricked him like that, will he still be willing to help us?
Angelia: Our business here is not done yet...
Naya: So it's over? Just heard about the election results from the vendors. Looks like you were able to keep your position as Chamber vice president!

Sherlock: How dare you laugh you double-crossing bastards?
You messed up my plans! I shall teach you guys a hard lesson!
Sherlock: D-Darn it, more gears for me to replace...
Angelia: Sir Sherlock, shall we return to my original request?.
Sherlock: You mess with me, and you still want me to do things for you!? In your dreams; now scram!
Angelia: If you refuse, I'm afraid you won't be maintaining your position as vice president.
Angelia: In the morning, you were trying to trick us into attacking the president of the Chamber. I recorded that conversation in this rune device.
Angelia: If the conversation in this is heard by other people, I wonder what the president and those merchants who oppose you will think?
Sherlock: WHAT!? That...how did you...
Sherlock: The appearance of that item...and the rune carved into it...it is indeed...
Sherlock: ... No, it cannot be. I don't believe it; you must be lying!
Angelia: You mentioned it yourself; how I'm very different compared to the first time we met. What makes you think I wouldn't do something like this?
Angelia: If you want proof, I don't mind broadcasting this for everyone to hear though~
Sherlock: YOU!
Karen: Sherlock.
Sherlock: President Karen? Why are you here?
Karen: One, I'm here for a reason, of course, no need for you to ask such a nonsensical question.
Karen: Two, I don't want to be here,

Karen: it's your escorts who asked me to come. 
So, what exactly is the issue you want me to take care of?
Naya: President Karen, we have here a──
Sherlock: ──Wait!
Sherlock: Y-Yes, it's little ol' me who wants to have a chat. Come, let's talk about it over there...
Elio: Princess, that rune device, is it really...?
Angelia: When we part ways in the desert, I returned to the Bazaar first with the purpose of finding this rune device.
Angelia: In order to fool Sherlock, it took quite the effort to find this.
Elio: Haha, I see...

Karen: ...In my opinion, you're a tin can who dreams of stealing my position, has no objections to using shady methods, 
yet always comes up with the stupidest plans.
Karen: However, since you sent people to protect me, I will apologize for now regarding my opinion of you.
Sherlock: (Here we go again, nobody knows if it's a compliment or an insult...)
Karen: However, regarding the expenses for the escort, I can't reimburse you through the Chamber. If I were to tell you the reasons, One...
Sherlock: Alright, alright, I get it. I'll cover the expenses myself...
Karen: The person that's not facing me, the one in the red cape, she's an escort as well?
Sherlock: ... Yes, she's the most expensive and sneakiest of the bunch. Therefore, unless the situation calls for it, I'd try to not get her involved...
Karen: ......
Karen: Understood. If that's all there is, I'll take my leave.
Angelia: Sir Sherlock, can we return to our previous discussion?
Sherlock: Fine, fine, you win! What do you want me to help with, fire away!
Angelia: Just want you to accompany us on a little trip to a particular location.
Sherlock: Stop beating around the bush! Just tell me where we are going!
Angelia: The mining grounds of the Dragoneye Gem...Atlas.
Sherlock: WHAT!?
